reviewText:
I've been waiting for this release for months since it leaked the rumor of FFIX being released on Steam. For this very reason I was really hyped even if I had a PS2 copy beside me for years and, when I finally got to play the remaster, I can only say that it's exactly as I expected it to be: it's a wonderful JRPG that was released in 2001 so it would have been surely limited by the age of the engine regardless of the remaster.
Honestly I didn't really like being forced to buy X-2 along with X as I probably wouldn't have done it if they were sold separately but in the end I would have happily paid â‚¬20 for X alone so it's not really an issue for me.
Anyway I've almost played it for 30 hours and I'm still at about 40-50% of the first game so I can't do anything but recommend it to every nostalgic player AND to everyone who didn't get to play the most beautiful Final Fantasy ever developed (IMHO).

Pros:
-Fantastic plot;
-Quite challenging;
-It takes a lot of hours to complete it at 100%.

Cons:
-Technical limitations due to the age of the game;
-RNG mechanics can be frustrating;
-It won't let you do anything else beside playing it.

X-2 is quite crappy but can be a palliative for all the players who got the absolute need of more of X after finishing the first. Honestly I didn't like the change in the mechanics at all and I'll only play it for the plot.
